verses.text_plain: My son, if thou be surety for thy friend, if thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,
verses.verse_html: 1My son, if thou be surety for thy friend, if thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,

verses.text_plain: Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.
verses.verse_html: 2Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.

verses.text_plain: Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend.
verses.verse_html:
3Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend. ▼
▼ and make…: or, so shalt thou prevail with thy friend

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and make…: or, so shalt thou prevail with thy friend
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and make…: or, so shalt thou prevail with thy friend

verses.text_plain: Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.
verses.verse_html: 4Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.

verses.text_plain: Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.
verses.verse_html: 5Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.

verses.text_plain: Go to the ant, thou sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise:
verses.verse_html: 6Go to the ant, thou sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise:

verses.text_plain: Which having no guide, overseer, or ruler,
verses.verse_html: 7Which having no guide, overseer, or ruler,

verses.text_plain: Provideth her meat in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest.
verses.verse_html: 8Provideth her meat in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest.

verses.text_plain: How long wilt thou sleep, O sluggard? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?
verses.verse_html: 9How long wilt thou sleep, O sluggard? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?

verses.text_plain: Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:
verses.verse_html: 10Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:

verses.text_plain: So shall thy poverty come as one that travelleth, and thy want as an armed man.
verses.verse_html: 11So shall thy poverty come as one that travelleth, and thy want as an armed man.

verses.text_plain: A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a froward mouth.
verses.verse_html: 12A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a froward mouth.

verses.text_plain: He winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers;
verses.verse_html: 13He winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers;

verses.text_plain: Frowardness is in his heart, he deviseth mischief continually; he soweth discord.
verses.verse_html:
14Frowardness is in his heart, he deviseth mischief continually; he soweth discord. ▼
▼ soweth: Heb. casteth forth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ soweth: Heb. casteth forth

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.
verses.verse_html: 15Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.

verses.text_plain: These six things doth the Lord hate: yea, seven are an abomination unto him:
verses.verse_html:
16These six things doth the Lord hate: yea, seven are an abomination unto him: ▼
▼ unto…: Heb. of his soul

footnotes.body_html: ▼ unto…: Heb. of his soul

verses.text_plain: A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood,
verses.verse_html:
17A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood, ▼
▼ A proud…: Heb. Haughty eyes

footnotes.body_html: ▼ A proud…: Heb. Haughty eyes

verses.text_plain: An heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to mischief,
verses.verse_html: 18An heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to mischief,

verses.text_plain: A false witness that speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.
verses.verse_html: 19A false witness that speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.

verses.text_plain: My son, keep thy father’s commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother:
verses.verse_html: 20My son, keep thy father’s commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother:

verses.text_plain: Bind them continually upon thine heart, and tie them about thy neck.
verses.verse_html: 21Bind them continually upon thine heart, and tie them about thy neck.

verses.text_plain: When thou goest, it shall lead thee; when thou sleepest, it shall keep thee; and when thou awakest, it shall talk with thee.
verses.verse_html: 22When thou goest, it shall lead thee; when thou sleepest, it shall keep thee; and when thou awakest, it shall talk with thee.

verses.text_plain: For the commandment is a lamp; and the law is light; and reproofs of instruction are the way of life:
verses.verse_html:
23For the commandment is a lamp; and the law is light; and reproofs of instruction are the way of life: ▼
▼ lamp: or, candle

verses.text_plain: To keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman.
verses.verse_html:
24To keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman. ▼
▼ of the…: or, of the strange tongue

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of the…: or, of the strange tongue
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of the…: or, of the strange tongue

verses.text_plain: Lust not after her beauty in thine heart; neither let her take thee with her eyelids.
verses.verse_html: 25Lust not after her beauty in thine heart; neither let her take thee with her eyelids.

verses.text_plain: For by means of a whorish woman a man is brought to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.
verses.verse_html:
26For by means of a whorish woman a man is brought to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life. ▼
▼ the adulteress: Heb. the woman of a man, or, a man’s wife

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the adulteress: Heb. the woman of a man, or, a man’s wife
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the adulteress: Heb. the woman of a man, or, a man’s wife

verses.text_plain: Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?
verses.verse_html: 27Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?

verses.text_plain: Can one go upon hot coals, and his feet not be burned?
verses.verse_html: 28Can one go upon hot coals, and his feet not be burned?

verses.text_plain: So he that goeth in to his neighbour’s wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.
verses.verse_html: 29So he that goeth in to his neighbour’s wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.

verses.text_plain: Men do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;
verses.verse_html: 30Men do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;

verses.text_plain: But if he be found, he shall restore sevenfold; he shall give all the substance of his house.
verses.verse_html: 31But if he be found, he shall restore sevenfold; he shall give all the substance of his house.

verses.text_plain: But whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding: he that doeth it destroyeth his own soul.
verses.verse_html:
32But whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding: he that doeth it destroyeth his own soul. ▼
▼ understanding: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: A wound and dishonour shall he get; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.
verses.verse_html: 33A wound and dishonour shall he get; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.

verses.text_plain: For jealousy is the rage of a man: therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.
verses.verse_html: 34For jealousy is the rage of a man: therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.

verses.text_plain: He will not regard any ransom; neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts.
verses.verse_html:
35He will not regard any ransom; neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts. ▼
▼ He will…: Heb. He will not accept the face of any ransom

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He will…: Heb. He will not accept the face of any ransom
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He will…: Heb. He will not accept the face of any ransom
